Namasu

Ingredients (Serves 2)

Vegetables
	•	200 g (7 oz) daikon radish, julienned
	•	80 g (2.8 oz) carrot, julienned

Seasoning
	•	3 g (1/2 tsp) fine sea salt
	•	30 ml (2 tbsp) rice vinegar
	•	12 g (1 tbsp) granulated sugar

Umami
	•	3 g (about 1 small strip) kombu

⸻

Method
	1.	Cut Vegetables
Julienne daikon and carrot into uniform matchsticks (about 3 mm thick, 6 cm long) for even texture and seasoning.
	2.	Salt & Draw Moisture
Toss vegetables with salt. Rest 10 minutes until moisture releases and vegetables soften slightly while remaining crisp.
	3.	Drain
Gently squeeze vegetables to remove excess liquid. Separate strands so they remain light and springy.
	4.	Season
Dissolve sugar in rice vinegar. Add kombu, then pour dressing over vegetables and toss to coat evenly. Rest 5 minutes.
	5.	Finish
Remove kombu before serving. Chill briefly or serve immediately, cold.

⸻

Optional Refinements
	•	Replace daikon with kohlrabi for a slightly sweeter crunch
	•	Use apple cider vinegar diluted 1:1 with water if rice vinegar is unavailable
	•	Add a few drops of yuzu or sudachi juice at the end for brighter citrus lift